pullRequest.body:
When trying to synthesize `IsEmpty` for a forall where the body is obviously nonempty, type class search can spend a lot of time trying to show that the domain is nonempty. Reordering the arguments changes the order in which type class search attempts to synthesize the arguments. This should speedup failing type class searches.

Following from a [Zulip conversation](https://leanprover.zulipchat.com/#narrow/channel/287929-mathlib4/topic/instances.20that.20match.20unconditionally/near/505787203)[#mathlib4 > instances that match unconditionally @ üí¨](https://leanprover.zulipchat.com/#narrow/channel/287929-mathlib4/topic/instances.20that.20match.20unconditionally/near/505787203)
